<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><presentation>V1 C V2 C V3 C</presentation>
<lyrics>[V1]
.  G                                   C                   G
 I come to the garden alone, While the dew is still on the roses;
.        D                    G              A7            D
 And the voice I hear falling on my ear, The Son of God discloses.

[C1]
.         G                     D
   And He walks with me, and He talks with me,
.         C        D7       G
   And He tells me I am His own;
.          G      B7          Em    C
   And the joy we share as we tarry there,
.       G         D7   G
   None other has ever known.

[V2]
.   G                                        C                          G
 He speaks, and the sound of His voice Is so sweet the birds hush their singing;
.        D              G               A7             D
 And the melody that He gave to me, Within my heart is ringing.

[V3]
.    G                                       C                  G
 I'd stay in the garden with Him, Though the night around me be falling;
.       D                    G                 A7             D
 But He bids me go; thru the voice of woe, His voice to me is calling.</lyrics>
<author>C. Austin Miles</author>
<key>G</key>
<title>In the Garden</title>
</song>